<title>INDONESIA: Indonesia says it will buy Russian warplanes.</title>
<headline>Indonesia says it will buy Russian warplanes.</headline>
<dateline>JAKARTA 1997-08-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Indonesia announced on Tuesday it would buy 12 Russian Sukhoi Su-30K fighter aircraft and eight Russian MI-17-1V helicopters as part of its defence modernisation.  </p>
<p>State Planning Minister Ginanjar Kartasasmita told a news conference the decision was made &quot;based on a study and comparison of various helicopters and fighter planes&quot;.</p>
<p>The announcement followed a decision in June to cancel a deal to buy nine U.S. F-16 jets following criticism in the American Congress of Indonesia's human rights record.</p>
<p>Indonesia had also studied the possibility of buying French or Swedish aircraft.</p>
